1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:07,960
All characters and events in this series are fictional
and created solely for entertainment purposes.
Viewer discretion is advised.

2
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:42,440
alright, so why did you call?

3
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,160
I only called to brag a little.

4
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:46,160
Ever since you became a brand ambassador for my company…

5
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:48,160
Our sales have shot up.

6
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:49,600
Ever since I came back after graduating

7
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:51,960
she’s seemed kind of tense with me all the time.

8
00:01:57,560 --> 00:02:00,320
It feels like we’ve drifted apart since you became famous.

9
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:02,560
Rumor has it a famous actress was seen

10
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:07,720
sneaking into a high-end condo with a mystery man.

11
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,320
Hello.

12
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:15,960
I don't know about how you’ve come this far and achieved this level of fame.

13
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,600
I'll excuse myself.

14
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:28,120
Why are you doing this, P'Flint?

15
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,079
Yes.

16
00:02:34,079 --> 00:02:35,440
That photo… it’s actually me.

17
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:49,120
The person in that photo is actually me.

18
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:54,360
Nop has come forward to confirm that the man
seen in the leaked photos sneaking into the actress’s condo

19
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,000
is him.

20
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:58,400
Are they just being shipped, or are they actually together?

21
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:03,440
Or is it exactly as social media detectives claim?

22
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:07,120
Why did that jerk give an interview like this?

23
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:10,680
I don’t even want to think about what P'Flint would say if she found out.

24
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:14,880
She knows, because she was here with me last night.

25
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:15,600
What?!

26
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:22,800
Is this just a fan ship, or the real deal or could the online detectives...

27
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,960
So what’s actually happening?

28
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:35,440
If you don’t have the courage to tell me the truth…

29
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,760
I’m going to confront him and find out the truth.

30
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:42,840
I don’t want to hear just one side of the story.

31
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:12,720
I’m not trying to stop you or afraid of you asking him.

32
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,200
I’m just hoping that…

33
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:19,360
you’ll believe what I say more than what anyone else says.

34
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,680
And should you just let people spread lies like that?

35
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,000
So that everyone ends up misunderstanding you?

36
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,600
If it’s not true

37
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,120
It’ll die down on its own.

38
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,360
Besides,

39
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:41,280
That kind of person isn’t someone I’d ever like.

40
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:52,600
Then what kind of person you like?

41
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,600
I'm just asking.

42
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,280
It didn’t mean anything.

43
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,920
Only you taking good care of yourself

44
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,520
and don’t put yourself in situations that could turn into bad press.

45
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,720
Yes.

46
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:20,840
I won’t let my news cause any damage to your company.

47
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:25,800
I’m getting sleepy. You can head back first if you want.

48
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,000
I’ll let Fey know.

49
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,800
It's alright.

50
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:35,240
Fey just called to say she’s almost done wrapping things up.

51
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,760
But if you're sleepy, you can go upstairs and sleep first.

52
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,480
Once Fey gets here, I’ll have her come upstairs and get you.

53
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:46,480
Thank you

54
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,360
You’re not telling me that…

55
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,200
Yup.

56
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,240
She stayed here all night waiting for you.

57
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:05,960
She just went back this morning.

58
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:07,240
For me?!

59
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:08,840
Exactly.

60
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:12,720
P'Flint said she’d wait for you so you two could talk things through
and clear up the news about me

61
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,760
before she goes into a meeting tomorrow.

62
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:18,160
Why are you acting like you have no idea what’s going on?

63
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:22,240
Of course I know.

64
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:23,760
I was just… curious…

65
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:26,080
I was working last night and accidentally fell asleep.

66
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:28,440
I woke up and rushed to shower, then came straight to see you.

67
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,840
Sorry

68
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,360
You don’t have to apologize to me.

69
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:34,200
Go apologize to P'Flint.

70
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:37,240
For making her have to sleep on the couch all night.

71
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:40,720
My sister?

72
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,960
the one who usually sleeps on an 800,000-baht mattress?

73
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:44,320
ended up on the couch?

74
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,159
Then where were you expecting her to sleep?

75
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:53,159
I thought you were going to let her sleep…

76
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:56,960
Okay, stop. I know what you’re thinking.

77
00:06:58,320 --> 00:07:00,760
Let’s go, or we’re going to be late.

78
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:02,840
If I’d known, I would’ve had P’Mooham come pick me up.

79
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:06,360
Oh come on, I was just teasing a little. Sun, wait… Sun…

80
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:15,160
What was that? Ahh. how many looks do we have today?

81
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:17,000
- We will have 3 looks for today.
- 3 looks. got it.

82
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,760
There’ll be a morning look, an afternoon look, and an evening look. same as usual.

83
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,920
Alright then, let's you can start getting ready.

84
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:25,720
Sun is here now. I’ll excuse myself. please go ahead. Thank you.

85
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:37,560
Hello, P’Mooham. I apologize for being late.

86
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:40,480
I think I stayed up a bit late last night.

87
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,560
I'm late because of you.

88
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:49,520
It’s okay. Sun only has two looks to shoot today, so it’ll be over pretty quickly.

89
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:52,720
Alright, let’s go then. The makeup and hair team is ready.

90
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,720
Okay.

91
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:56,640
Then you go in first. I’ll park the car and catch up with you.

92
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:57,800
See you.

93
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:03,800
Okay, Sun. You’ll walk over there, and then we’ll do a bit more shooting right here.

94
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,040
Okay.

95
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,240
I must’ve been really lucky.

96
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,400
Hey. You.

97
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,960
Excuse me, this is the staff parking area.

98
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:49,560
You’re not supposed to park here like this.

99
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:54,120
I got here first, so I parked first. What’s wrong with that?

100
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,800
But this spot is for the staff…

101
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,760
Fine

102
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:50,800
Seriously, why are you parking it so close?

103
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:54,880
Excuse me.

104
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,040
You.

105
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,280
Why do you park so close?

106
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:00,600
You.

107
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:04,440
Why are you parking it so close. How am I gonna get out of my car.

108
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:06,920
Please move your car.

109
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,200
You.

110
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:11,960
You.

111
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:19,040
Excuse me, I can’t get out unless you move your car.
Please come back and move it first.

112
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,080
You.

113
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:27,480
If you’d parked properly in the first place, this wouldn’t have happened.

114
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:35,120
(Parking Lot)

115
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,360
What kind of person are you?

116
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,760
You mess up and then have the nerve to snap at other people?

117
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:50,520
Hey! you could’ve just said it nicely from the start.

118
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,080
But I can’t get out of the car.

119
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:02,960
Hey. come back. You…

120
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:07,800
This hairstyle looks really good.

121
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:15,400
Fey, what happened to you? Why do you look like this?

122
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,280
I ran into a crazy person.

123
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:22,560
But never mind. Let’s just blame it on the Thai's weather.

124
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,920
The more I talk about it, the more annoyed I get.

125
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:31,000
Excuse me. Khun Peach would like to come in and explain today’s shooting concept.

126
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:32,800
Khun Peach said it won’t take long.

127
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:35,520
- Sure, thank you very much.
- Yes.

128
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,600
Perfect!

129
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,360
I’m actually looking forward to meeting Khun Peach.

130
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:48,200
They say Khun Peach is good-looking, polite, and really talented too.

131
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:52,800
Every project Peach takes on is with top international brands.

132
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,800
But this is a Thai brand. Why did she take the job?

133
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,480
I’m not sure either.

134
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:03,840
But I overheard the staff saying that…

135
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:08,040
Apparently, Khun Peach specifically asked the client for Sun on this job.

136
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:10,360
Umm. I think...

137
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:13,400
I’m pretty sure Khun Peach has a crush on Sun.

138
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,480
I don’t think it’s like that.

139
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:20,520
I think she’s just choosing based on suitability.

140
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:24,120
I don’t think Sun would be interested anyway.

141
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:27,680
I’ve known Sun for a long time, and I’ve only ever seen her interested in…

142
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:31,640
Oh my... Nop right?

143
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:38,040
I saw an interview. Well, one interview and it was trending as a couple for days.

144
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:50,440
Um… that was probably just fan service for a ship.

145
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:53,680
What I mean is, Sun only cares about work.

146
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:58,120
Looks like I’m the only one who’s totally open to it.

147
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:02,920
- Hello!
- Hello!

148
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:04,920
Hello!

149
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:09,200
Hello, Sun. I’m Peach, the photographer for today.

150
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,680
It’s a pleasure to officially meet you.

151
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:15,200
Hello, Khun Peach. It’s nice to officially meet you as well.

152
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:21,680
I’ll give you a quick brief first, so I won’t take up too much of everyone’s time.

153
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:26,200
The concept for today’s shoot is the launch of a new fragrance.

154
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:30,080
The product will be released this March under the Sense of the Sun campaign.

155
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:34,480
The mood and tone will be bright, summery, and fresh with a touch of elegance.

156
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,960
High-fashion inspired, yet easy to relate to.

157
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:40,920
I’ll focus more on the vibe and natural moments rather than fixed poses.

158
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,160
I’d like the overall look to feel as natural as possible.

159
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:44,600
So when someone looks at the pictures…

160
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,960
they’ll be drawn to Sun Atita’s unique charm.

161
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:49,320
Then this perfume collection is the one they need.

162
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,480
Do you have any questions, Sun?

163
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,520
No, I don’t.

164
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:55,360
But if there’s anything Khun Peach'd like me to adjust on set,

165
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,680
please feel free to let me know.

166
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:58,720
You can call me P'Peach.

167
00:13:59,560 --> 00:14:01,000
I’ll be waiting on set, then.

168
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:02,560
Sure thing

169
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:13,960
Why did you leave in such a hurry that day?

170
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:18,200
I still haven’t returned your lipstick.

171
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:38,000
Why did you leave the bar so early that day?

172
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,880
I didn’t even get a chance to return your lipstick.

173
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:46,000
Let’s go, Sun.

174
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:48,600
I think we should go check the set again.

175
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,600
Sun.

176
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:52,520
Since when did you get to know that Khun Peach?

177
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:56,040
I already told you. I’ve never met her before.

178
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,960
We literally just met today.

179
00:14:58,440 --> 00:15:00,560
But he said she met you at the bar

180
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:01,840
And what about this lipstick?

181
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:04,120
Can’t you tell just by the color?

182
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:06,960
You know I don’t wear this color unless it’s for work.

183
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:08,920
And there’s one more thing.

184
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,160
You also know,

185
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,600
that I don't drink.

186
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:13,760
Why would I go to a bar?

187
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,320
That's make sense.

188
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:20,240
But I feel like there’s something off about that person.

189
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:22,800
Or...

190
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:25,040
She's a psycho!?

191
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:26,120
Oh my...!

192
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,920
I don't think so.

193
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:33,360
Maybe she just met someone who looks like you.
Like the person in those leaked photos.

194
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,760
Don’t worry about it too much, Khun Fey.

195
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,360
We’re ready on set, Sun.

196
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:38,320
Okay.

197
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:39,840
We'll you at the set.

198
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:41,280
Let's go

199
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:54,280
You’ve got this, Sun.

200
00:15:58,440 --> 00:16:03,680
Let me take this one for a moment. Let’s make the composition a bit more…
composed, okay

201
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,040
Yes. P'Flint?

202
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:07,440
How is it going?

203
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:11,280
I think I should be asking you how you’re doing, P'Flint.

204
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:14,640
I heard you stayed up all night taking care of Sun, didn’t you?

205
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:22,360
Didn't you tell me you think she might be being stalked?

206
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,720
I thought you said you were worried about your friend.

207
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:27,360
It’s not strange for me to worry about my friend.

208
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:29,760
But you... you're worried about her.

209
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:31,680
I'm worried about the company.

210
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:35,600
The leaked photos issue isn’t over yet. If something else happens now,
it’ll just make things even more complicated.

211
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,560
But it’s good that you are with her.

212
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:41,280
I’ll have my secretary send you the daily
summary about today’s situation at the company.

213
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,840
Oh my, Sun, you look so beautiful!

214
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:57,280
I have a feeling the photographer today was a bit… strange.

215
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:00,640
How strange?

216
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:03,560
She just returned Sun’s lipstick a moment ago.

217
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:06,119
She said Sun had left it behind, even though they’d just met for the first time.

218
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,440
Isn’t that a bit strange?

219
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:10,960
That’s all for now, P'Flint.

220
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:13,880
If you have so many questions, why don’t you come yourself?

221
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:27,760
Pretty. Do you mind if I take a quick look at this one?

222
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:29,680
Yeah, right?

223
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:31,680
Yes! wow, this photo is gorgeous.

224
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,440
Beautiful.

225
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,320
Let me adjust the composition a bit.

226
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:38,920
This photo looks really good.

227
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:43,320
Khun Fey, the photo is really beautiful. Please have a look.

228
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:46,600
It’s beautiful. I like this one too, the one that we used as a reference.

229
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:48,560
- I think it's good.
- Yes, this one

230
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:49,960
and also this one.

231
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,560
Could you open up to the camera a little?

232
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:55,920
P'Mooham.

233
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:56,680
Yes?

234
00:17:56,680 --> 00:18:00,080
Don’t you think it looks a bit too intimate?

235
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:04,280
Hmm...

236
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:06,560
I think it's okay.

237
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:09,560
If we don’t set the composition like this, the shot won’t be perfect.

238
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:11,200
I think this is good as it is.

239
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:13,680
Pretty.

240
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:16,160
But I think that Peach girl…

241
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:18,320
There’s something strange about her.

242
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:22,360
Hmm… I don’t think it’s that strange, Khun Fey.

243
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:24,080
She seems quite professional.

244
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:26,080
Take a look. It’s really beautiful.

245
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,520
- You look absolutely beautiful, Sun.
- Gorgeous!

246
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,160
Very good.

247
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:37,760
The photo looks great, but…

248
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:38,920
t’s beautiful.

249
00:18:40,040 --> 00:18:41,200
Could you lift your chin a little more, please?

250
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,320
Oh my!

251
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:44,600
Good.

252
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:51,680
That set is done. I think we’ll have plenty of photos to choose from.

253
00:18:58,080 --> 00:18:59,320
It's okay.

254
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:02,760
I’ll take care of it.

255
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:04,640
- Could you stand up, Sun?
- Sun, come here.

256
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:09,880
Alright, Sun, go get changed. I’ll have the crew set the lights.

257
00:19:09,880 --> 00:19:11,400
Sure thing.

258
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,720
I’m about to order drinks. Do you want anything, Sun?

259
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:14,640
It’s alright.

260
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:17,880
Because she doesn’t take food from strangers

261
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:21,560
Come on, Sun. Let’s shoot quickly so we can wrap this up.

262
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:25,040
Sure.

263
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:46,960
Why did you talk to Khun Peach like that, Khun Fey?

264
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:50,320
I don’t really like Khun Peach, to be honest.

265
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:52,720
I don’t know… it seems like she’s using her authority inappropriately.

266
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:55,000
What’s going on, Fey?

267
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:58,760
Didn’t you just meet her today? Why do you already dislike her?

268
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:01,320
Hey, look at how she looks at you.

269
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:03,800
It’s like she’s about to eat you alive.

270
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,560
You’re exaggerating.

271
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:07,000
I think…

272
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:09,320
It seems normal to me.

273
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,640
She also seems…

274
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:13,920
polite.

275
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:16,080
This is normal to you?

276
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:17,800
She’s clearly a psycho.

277
00:20:18,840 --> 00:20:23,440
Anyway, if that lipstick isn’t really yours, I’ll return it to her myself after we’re done.

278
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:27,840
I think it’d be better if we go change clothes.

279
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:30,760
We’ve got more hair and makeup to do, let’s go.

280
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,040
Um… Sun,

281
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:40,600
Um… Fey won’t cause any problems with the job, will she?

282
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,640
Don’t worry, P’Mooham.

283
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:48,160
But if it’s her sister… I wouldn’t be so sure.

284
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,960
That one doesn’t really talk much.

285
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:53,200
She prefers actions over words.

286
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:57,400
Oh my god, just hearing you say that gives me goosebumps, Sun.

287
00:21:09,520 --> 00:21:12,760
Um, excuse me, what’s going on here?

288
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:17,960
Um, there’s an urgent meeting going on right now, but don’t worry.
it won’t affect the shoot at all.

289
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,480
Sun, are you okay with that?

290
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:23,280
If you’re not okay with it, we can pause the shoot for now.

291
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:25,920
It’s okay. I can keep shooting. I’m totally fine.

292
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,320
Alright, let’s continue shooting.

293
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:29,760
- Alright, Sun, You'll…
- Right here.

294
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:34,080
Just pose naturally, Sun.

295
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:38,280
What kind of person brings a meeting room into a studio?

296
00:21:38,280 --> 00:21:39,480
Exactly.

297
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:41,920
Everything went really well today.

298
00:22:32,840 --> 00:22:35,480
I think the Sun kiss-skin look really suits you, Sun. Keeping it this soft is just right.

299
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:38,720
P'Flint...

300
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,200
P'Flint...

301
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,280
What are you doing here!?

302
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:50,800
The meeting. Did you forget?

303
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:51,680
Huh?

304
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:54,560
We have a big project meeting at the company today.

305
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:56,880
How could there not be a deputy managing director?

306
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:00,880
You said you were busy, so I moved the meeting here instead.

307
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,880
But they’re working right now.

308
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:07,120
If you do this, P'Flint, Sun’s clients might complain.

309
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:09,560
Oh, you’re here already?

310
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:12,600
It’s been a long time, Flint.

311
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:14,920
Hey, Jane. How’ve you been?

312
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:16,240
I’m good.

313
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:20,240
Don’t tell me that’s… Fey?

314
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,360
Umm.

315
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:23,560
No wonder she looked familiar.

316
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:26,280
I was going to say hi at first, but I was afraid I might be mistaken.

317
00:23:26,280 --> 00:23:29,760
Ah, hello, P’Jane.

318
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:31,440
Since you all know each other so well,

319
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:32,920
feel free to make yourselves comfortable.

320
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:36,640
- Sure thing.
- I’ve had the staff prepare the meeting room already.

321
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:38,160
- Sorry for the inconvenience.
- It's okay.

322
00:23:42,280 --> 00:23:46,680
I’d like to present the concept of our new car model,
which is currently in the prototype development phase.

323
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:49,200
We’ve named it the Aurora Vanta.

324
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:52,040
t’s an ultra-luxury vehicle.

325
00:23:52,360 --> 00:23:57,520
The target audience is high-level leaders with power and exceptional taste.

326
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:03,560
But it’s a dream brought to life on the road for today’s generation.

327
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:07,000
The projected price range will be approximately 15 to 20 million baht.

328
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:09,080
Too high.

329
00:24:15,040 --> 00:24:17,640
I think the price is set far too high.

330
00:24:18,280 --> 00:24:23,840
Also, the target group you’re aiming
for makes up only about 1% of the population in Thailand.

331
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:27,800
We’ve invested significant resources
and time in the production and design of this model

332
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:31,720
Yet we’re about to sell it to a group of people who will hardly ever actually drive it.

333
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:39,240
I think we should set the price at around 8 to 10 million baht.

334
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:42,560
I agree with that.

335
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:48,680
At around the 20-million-baht price point,
global brands already hold a strong grip on the market.

336
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:52,200
Competing in that segment is not an easy task.

337
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,880
Feel free to adjust your position, Sun.

338
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:02,960
You can move your body in your own style.

339
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:04,240
Sure.

340
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:10,360
If we lower the price that much, it could diminish our brand value.

341
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:14,400
Especially since this is the first model we’ve developed and manufactured in-house.

342
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:19,560
It could potentially damage the premium brand image we’ve built.

343
00:25:22,880 --> 00:25:24,680
Stop. Stop .Stop

344
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:32,200
Stop worrying about the brand image.

345
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:35,560
Doing this is what will truly give us life in the market.

346
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:38,960
I want us to be absolutely clear that we’re not just a luxury brand.

347
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:41,760
But a brand that truly understands the customers we care about most.

348
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:44,920
Because value isn’t always defined by price.

349
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:53,480
Alright, that’s a wrap.

350
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:55,000
Thank you so much, everyone.

351
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:58,080
You look so beautiful, Sun.

352
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:06,840
P'Flint...

353
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:09,920
P'Flint...

354
00:26:09,920 --> 00:26:11,360
What are you looking at?

355
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:16,600
Let’s move to the dressing room. I’ll take...

356
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:20,360
I’m just thinking.

357
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:37,720
Your outfit is ready in the dressing room, Sun.

358
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:42,000
I’m going to discuss the payment paperwork with the client first. I’ll be back.

359
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,640
- Is that okay?
- Yes. P'Mooham.

360
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,200
Okay. Perfect.

361
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:52,600
Sorry my company ended up holding the meeting here today.

362
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:53,960
Everything got so chaotic.

363
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:55,440
It’s no big deal.

364
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:58,720
What about you, did P'Flint scold you?

365
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:01,280
You don’t normally forget about work like this.

366
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:03,120
So why did you forget today?

367
00:27:03,320 --> 00:27:04,360
I didn’t…

368
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:15,440
P'Flint...

369
00:27:24,320 --> 00:27:27,920
Fey, could you help me tie this real quick?

370
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:45,640
I think Sun kiss-skin look is just right with such light makeup.

371
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:53,120
You think...

372
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:57,200
Why did P’Flint do that?

373
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:00,760
Do you think she knows...

374
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:02,760
What she did…

375
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:06,160
it made me feel…

376
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,640
Feel like what?

377
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:29,400
How did you come in here?

378
00:28:30,440 --> 00:28:32,440
I saw you calling Fey, but she wasn’t here.

379
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:35,680
So… what exactly did I do?

380
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:44,120
Sun, are you done with your outfit yet?

381
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:45,880
Is there anything I can help you with?

382
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:49,400
It’s okay, P’Mooham. I’ve just finished changing.

383
00:28:51,080 --> 00:28:53,000
P’Flint, could you stay a moment?

384
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:55,280
I don’t want P’Mooham to be startled.

385
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:07,800
Alright. Let me see...

386
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:13,360
I’ll take you to greet the client first, okay? Then we can head home and get some rest.

387
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:14,920
Okay.

388
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,280
Let's go.

389
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:24,120
This one’s nice.

390
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:25,880
Could I see the photo below?

391
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:28,280
This is the photo Khun Peach asked us to keep aside.

392
00:29:28,280 --> 00:29:29,840
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

393
00:29:29,840 --> 00:29:31,800
- Please pass these along to the crew as well.
- Sure.

394
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:42,840
Refreshing.

395
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:44,120
So refreshing.

396
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,000
I think it’s good.

397
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:49,000
You can go help the crew pack up.

398
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,200
Sure, P’Peach.

399
00:29:58,240 --> 00:29:59,880
Here, I’m giving this back.

400
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:01,120
She said it's not hers

401
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:05,520
Did Sun say that, or did you?

402
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:08,520
Let me tell you something.

403
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:09,720
I’m Sun’s close friend.

404
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:12,200
I know her well. She doesn’t wear this shade of lipstick,

405
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,640
and she doesn’t go to clubs.

406
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:17,080
So whatever that obvious flirting is trying to pick fights just to start a conversation

407
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:19,680
you should stop. It doesn’t work.

408
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:24,480
And what you’re doing to me right now…

409
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:26,520
is that another one of those obvious flirting tactics?

410
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:29,120
Hey, you.

411
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:36,520
You should keep it for yourself, Khun Fey.

412
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:38,320
Maybe it’ll make you look prettier.

413
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:45,040
Hey, you!

414
00:30:48,160 --> 00:30:51,840
It looks really good on you, Sun. Don’t you think so? Both looks, right?

415
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:53,440
But honestly, Sun looks great today.

416
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:54,880
- Really?
- That’s good.

417
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:55,840
Sun.

418
00:30:57,080 --> 00:30:59,080
Are you going anywhere after this?

419
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:02,120
- Would you like to have dinner together?
- not available.

420
00:31:03,040 --> 00:31:05,000
She already has plans.

421
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:18,360
She has a work meeting with P’Flint.

422
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:20,640
Maybe next time, Khun Peach.

423
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:23,240
Sun. Let's go.

424
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:25,120
Come on, let's go.

425
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:27,080
Come on, let's go.

426
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:31,120
Goodbye.

427
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:35,800
I'll see you again soon, Sun.

428
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:48,160
Give me a call, Sun.

429
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,600
I’m back in my room now.

430
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:03,480
Okay. Sun.

431
00:32:04,280 --> 00:32:06,000
What was the meeting about?

432
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:11,240
It was about a new advertising project.

433
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:13,520
I’ll summarize it for P'Mooham later.

434
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:14,560
Is there any problem?

435
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:17,680
Or are you busy sending messages to your shipped co-star?

436
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:20,840
I was talking about work with P’Mooham.

437
00:32:21,560 --> 00:32:26,200
And I don’t need to report to anyone.

438
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:28,600
I think that’s normal.

439
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:32,680
When people are in a relationship, they usually text each other about where they are.

440
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:34,960
Just in case you might want him to come and see you.

441
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:36,840
So I can get back right away.

442
00:32:38,840 --> 00:32:43,160
If you’re referring to yesterday’s interview, I’ve already discussed it with P’Mooham.

443
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:45,360
She told me that…

444
00:32:45,360 --> 00:32:51,320
The channel also see it as a positive thing, since it helps promote the series that
P’Nop and I are working on together.

445
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:53,920
So you’re saying you won’t deny what happened?

446
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:56,720
Even if the channel approves of this…

447
00:32:57,240 --> 00:33:00,040
That doesn’t mean you can just walk into a man’s condo
without caring about how it looks to others.

448
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:09,080
I used to think you would trust what I said more than this.

449
00:33:11,160 --> 00:33:12,680
But now I see it clearly.

450
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,120
No matter how much I explain…

451
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:19,160
You’ll probably believe whatever you want to believe.

452
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:21,120
Right?

453
00:33:26,320 --> 00:33:28,320
Then I suppose I should apologize.

454
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:31,200
for causing trouble for your company again

455
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:33,960
I’ll excuse myself.

456
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:18,560
What's up, Fey.

457
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:21,239
Do you know that Nop was at the studio today?

458
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:22,600
What!?

459
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:24,719
And he didn’t come alone.

460
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:27,880
He even showed up with reporters in tow, carrying a bouquet of flowers.

461
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:30,679
Good thing P'Flint took you back earlier.

462
00:34:30,679 --> 00:34:33,600
Otherwise, the news about you two dating would’ve been even bigger by now.

463
00:34:35,520 --> 00:34:38,000
So… are you still staying with P'Flint?

464
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:41,120
She’s already gone back.

465
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:44,000
She probably didn’t want to see my face any longer.

466
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:50,280
Maybe I’m just a problem to her.

467
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:08,800
How’s it going?

468
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:12,720
Nop has already gone into the condo. He hasn’t gone anywhere else.

469
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:17,280
If there’s any movement in the meantime, I’ll inform you right away.

470
00:35:18,160 --> 00:35:19,320
Thank you so much.

471
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:48,240
Ah...

472
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:50,880
Ah.. This outfit right?

473
00:36:53,160 --> 00:36:54,880
Let me take a look.

474
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:57,080
Oh my!

475
00:36:57,080 --> 00:36:59,240
Your makeup looks amazing. Your skin looks so flawless.

476
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:03,120
What powder are you using?

477
00:37:03,480 --> 00:37:05,080
It’s Aura Rich, P’Mooham.

478
00:37:06,080 --> 00:37:08,080
Oh, can I try it?

479
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:12,000
You can use mine if you’d like, P’Mooham.

480
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:14,880
I’ll try it then, Sun. Thank you so much.

481
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:20,360
Oh, it’s so smooth. Does it look good on me?

482
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:23,640
- It looks beautiful! Oh wow, it’s so smooth.
- It’s so smooth and finely textured.

483
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:25,680
Oh...

484
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:27,760
I bought this for you.

485
00:37:28,040 --> 00:37:29,320
you had a shoot this early in the morning like this,

486
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:31,720
A cup of coffee would probably help you feel more refreshed.

487
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:35,000
Thank you very much.

488
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:37,320
Wow, you two are so sweet.

489
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:40,920
Taking such good care of each other like this… I think you’re ready to go public.

490
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:43,560
Come on, don’t tease us.

491
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:45,520
Oh, no need to be shy.

492
00:37:45,520 --> 00:37:49,520
Sun, there’s an updated script. I hurried to bring it to you so you could read it first.

493
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:51,240
What’s the new script about?

494
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:54,760
They’ve added two more characters to bring more color to the story.

495
00:37:55,200 --> 00:37:57,000
Really? How come I didn’t know about this?

496
00:37:57,360 --> 00:37:58,360
May I take a look?

497
00:38:07,560 --> 00:38:09,000
This way, please.

498
00:38:09,480 --> 00:38:11,800
They’re here. The new actors have arrived.

499
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:14,720
Hello, everyone. Hello. Nice to meet you.

500
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:16,240
Hello, P’Nop.

501
00:38:16,680 --> 00:38:19,560
Hello, P’Sun. I’m Irene.

502
00:38:19,560 --> 00:38:21,080
And my name is Natcha.

503
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:24,400
We’re both really happy to be working with you, P’Sun.

504
00:38:24,400 --> 00:38:28,360
I’ve been a fan of yours since your very first project.

505
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:32,760
If there’s anything you’d like us to adjust, don’t hesitate to tell us.

506
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:34,520
Of course.

507
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:36,480
These are the scripts for the two of you.

508
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:37,880
Thank you.

509
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:52,720
Where do you think you’re going?

510
00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:56,520
Didn’t you say it yourself that you didn’t want to talk to me?

511
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:59,400
I’ll go somewhere you won’t have to see me.

512
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:03,680
But we’re not done talking yet.

513
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:05,920
You don’t have the right to walk away from me like this.

514
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:08,040
Because you’re my person.

515
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:11,720
Didn’t you say you hated me?

516
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:13,120
You said you didn’t want to see me.

517
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:15,640
Then why do you keep meddling in my life like this?

518
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:18,280
What do you want from me, exactly?

519
00:39:20,240 --> 00:39:21,240
You really want to know?

520
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:22,840
About what I really want.

521
00:39:24,360 --> 00:39:25,480
Fine.

522
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:34,520
Cut. Cut. Cut.

523
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:46,320
Hey, the blocking for you two isn’t supposed to be like this.

524
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:49,440
According to the script, you two are supposed to be watching from over there, right?

525
00:39:51,320 --> 00:39:55,360
I’m sorry. We’re still new, so please don’t be upset with us, P’Nop.

526
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:59,200
I just didn’t see anything like this in the scene.

527
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:01,760
But it looked like you were about to kiss her.

528
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:04,960
So we misunderstood and thought the scene
had been changed and needed to be reshoot.

529
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:06,880
I sincerely apologize.

530
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:10,200
That’s true.

531
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:12,400
At first, even I was a bit confused.

532
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:14,760
Maybe you mixed up the scenes, P’Nop?

533
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:20,120
Then please don’t scold them.

534
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:24,960
Okay, let’s reset and take it from the top.

535
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:26,800
Stay focused. Don’t miss your cue again.

536
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,560
One more time.

537
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:30,960
Reset, reset!

538
00:40:33,120 --> 00:40:35,600
Could you touch up her makeup for them, please?

539
00:40:48,600 --> 00:40:49,440
Good afternoon.

540
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:50,600
Good afternoon.

541
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:54,680
I’m Paabfah from Rafah Import Supercar. We’ll be providing the car for today’s scene.

542
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:56,800
I’m the producer of this production.

543
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:59,200
I didn’t expect you to come here in person, Khun Paabfah.

544
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:01,440
don’t usually come here myself.

545
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:04,240
I heard it was Sun’s here, so I decided to come myself.

546
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:10,320
As for the car for today’s scene, our staff have already parked it at the ramp.
The crew can proceed with the setup.

547
00:41:10,640 --> 00:41:11,960
Thank you very much.

548
00:41:14,360 --> 00:41:15,840
And where is Sun right now?

549
00:41:16,280 --> 00:41:17,440
I was thinking of giving her a little surprise.

550
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:20,560
She’s getting a touch-up right now. she should be almost done.

551
00:41:20,560 --> 00:41:21,640
Please come this way.

552
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:26,280
Next time during rehearsals, please keep an eye on it.

553
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:28,280
Mistakes like this cost the crew time.

554
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:32,840
And if anything were to happen to P’Nop,
the production wouldn’t be able to take responsibility.

555
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:35,160
My apologies.

556
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:53,920
What’s up, Fey?

557
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:55,680
What’s wrong with you?

558
00:41:56,160 --> 00:41:58,840
I understand that Sun is the company’s brand ambassador.

559
00:41:59,560 --> 00:42:02,880
But bringing your own people into the set like this…

560
00:42:03,240 --> 00:42:06,800
It feels like an excessive intrusion into both Sun’s work and personal life.

561
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:11,040
Since the incident at the photoshoot meeting last time,
I haven’t had the chance to clear things up with you yet

562
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:13,040
You’ve met Irene and Natcha already, right?

563
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:16,600
Why are you doing this, P’Flint?

564
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:20,720
Why are you suddenly so involved in everything about Sun?

565
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:25,360
When you never showed any interest or concern before.

566
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:28,280
We’ll talk later, Fey. I need to head to a meeting.

567
00:42:50,080 --> 00:42:51,200
I’m sorry.

568
00:42:52,200 --> 00:42:54,800
I didn’t think P’Flint would use her authority as a sponsor…

569
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:58,880
to negotiate with the production, demand script changes,
and even bring his own people onto the set like this.

570
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:03,120
It’s not your fault.

571
00:43:04,320 --> 00:43:06,840
She probably doesn’t fully understand how my work process works.

572
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:10,560
I hope the network doesn’t find out about this.

573
00:43:11,080 --> 00:43:15,200
Because if they do, the channel and your company, Rafah,
will definitely end up having problems.

574
00:43:15,880 --> 00:43:19,320
Especially with you being in the middle, it only makes things harder for you.

575
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:24,360
t doesn’t seem that hard.

576
00:43:26,400 --> 00:43:27,760
We’re just turning rumors into facts.

577
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:30,120
Sun is just dating me.

578
00:43:31,840 --> 00:43:33,680
he buzz is good. The network’s happy.

579
00:43:33,920 --> 00:43:36,800
That way, outsiders won’t interfere.

580
00:43:37,320 --> 00:43:38,080
Isn't that true?

581
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:50,320
Alright.

582
00:43:50,640 --> 00:43:51,360
Thank you.

583
00:43:55,200 --> 00:43:56,680
P’Pang, may I talk to you for a moment?

584
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:58,240
Is there something you need, Nop?

585
00:44:00,120 --> 00:44:02,320
What’s going on with these new characters that were added?

586
00:44:03,480 --> 00:44:07,640
Um… the director and the writing team felt that the script was still lacking some color.

587
00:44:07,640 --> 00:44:09,160
So they made a few small adjustments.

588
00:44:09,160 --> 00:44:10,920
Is there something bothering you, Nop?

589
00:44:11,640 --> 00:44:13,400
Wasn’t this requested by the sponsor?

590
00:44:14,520 --> 00:44:17,280
I’m genuinely curious how much they invested,

591
00:44:17,280 --> 00:44:21,880
for the production to dare risk changing the script despite
the potential fallout with the network.

592
00:44:23,480 --> 00:44:25,280
Uh… I mean…

593
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:28,400
The sponsor you’re talking about… is it Khun Rafah Supawaret?

594
00:44:29,240 --> 00:44:31,200
So I can report it to the network properly.

595
00:44:34,720 --> 00:44:35,760
P'Pang.

596
00:44:35,760 --> 00:44:39,120
You know how this needs to be handled, right?

597
00:44:40,400 --> 00:44:41,720
Yes.

598
00:44:56,760 --> 00:44:57,760
I’m sorry.

599
00:44:58,880 --> 00:45:00,800
I’m sorry that I only just realized I’m in love with you.

600
00:45:03,080 --> 00:45:04,480
I’ve loved you all along.

601
00:45:06,960 --> 00:45:08,600
Can you give me one more chance?

602
00:45:28,760 --> 00:45:30,520
(Just for now)

603
00:45:31,960 --> 00:45:33,720
We’ve done everything we could.

604
00:45:37,040 --> 00:45:39,160
It seems like the love scene tonight won’t really make a difference.

605
00:46:11,120 --> 00:46:12,360
What are you doing here, P’Flint?

606
00:46:18,840 --> 00:46:23,680
Do you know that I already know you were the one
who brought those two into the production.

607
00:46:24,440 --> 00:46:25,760
With sponsor conditions attached.

608
00:46:28,640 --> 00:46:31,320
Even if Sun doesn’t say anything, I can tell.

609
00:46:31,640 --> 00:46:32,800
…that she’s angry.

610
00:46:37,080 --> 00:46:38,440
I was just making an offer.

611
00:46:39,120 --> 00:46:40,480
But I didn’t force anyone.

612
00:46:41,280 --> 00:46:44,360
You can’t say this is entirely my fault, Fey.

613
00:46:44,720 --> 00:46:46,920
P’Flint, are you going to keep working through other people like this?

614
00:46:51,600 --> 00:46:53,240
What exactly do you want?

615
00:46:58,320 --> 00:46:59,600
Good evening, Khun Rafah.

616
00:47:05,080 --> 00:47:06,680
Are you here to check on the love scene?

617
00:47:11,200 --> 00:47:12,760
But it seems you’re a bit late.

618
00:47:14,160 --> 00:47:16,160
But all things considered, I’m very impressed.

619
00:47:17,440 --> 00:47:20,080
Impressed enough that I’d even give it a free review.

620
00:47:21,720 --> 00:47:24,280
The car is spacious, and the seats recline really well.

621
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:25,720
And the seats are really comfortable.

622
00:47:25,720 --> 00:47:27,600
Let’s go home and enjoy an onsen soak.

623
00:47:49,360 --> 00:47:50,400
Sun...

624
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:55,840
If you want me to pick you up after the wrap on Thursday, just let me know.

625
00:47:57,840 --> 00:47:59,760
As for today, you did a great job.

626
00:48:00,200 --> 00:48:01,840
When we were in the scene together…

627
00:48:01,840 --> 00:48:03,440
Even the crew were blushing.

628
00:48:04,120 --> 00:48:06,800
I think once it’s on air, the buzz will be really good.

629
00:48:10,440 --> 00:48:11,560
I’ll excuse myself then.

630
00:48:12,000 --> 00:48:13,560
You should hurry back and get some rest, Sun.

631
00:48:16,520 --> 00:48:18,160
Did you get to perform the way we practiced together?

632
00:48:25,600 --> 00:48:26,480
Yes?

633
00:48:29,040 --> 00:48:32,840
I’m asking, did you perform it the way we practiced together?

634
00:48:33,840 --> 00:48:35,120
Like how?

635
00:49:49,040 --> 00:49:50,400
Dear Diary,

636
00:49:50,800 --> 00:49:52,320
Today is the last day.

637
00:49:52,320 --> 00:49:54,320
I’ll get to wear my school uniform.

638
00:49:55,320 --> 00:49:56,360
You know

639
00:49:56,520 --> 00:49:57,680
that the best thing is…

640
00:49:58,120 --> 00:50:00,880
It’s not about not having to wake up early for school anymore.

641
00:50:01,840 --> 00:50:04,400
It’s probably getting my very first bouquet of flowers.

642
00:50:04,760 --> 00:50:07,320
From someone I never even thought I’d receive one from.

643
00:50:08,080 --> 00:50:11,440
Thank you, P’Flint.

644
00:50:16,520 --> 00:50:18,880
You don’t have to believe what I’m saying, P’Flint.

645
00:50:19,400 --> 00:50:21,200
But I want you to know that…

646
00:50:22,040 --> 00:50:26,200
I’m a person too, not something you can do whatever you want to.

647
00:50:26,840 --> 00:50:30,880
What you did… you might not have thought much of it, or felt anything at all.

648
00:50:30,880 --> 00:50:32,880
But I think Sun might not see it that way.

649
00:50:33,320 --> 00:50:37,520
Khun Peach contacted the channel directly, so P’Mooham couldn’t really turn it down.

650
00:50:37,880 --> 00:50:39,360
If you can’t refuse on your own…

651
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:41,560
Then we just have to make her choose someone else.

652
00:50:42,560 --> 00:50:45,560
You’ll have to pick me up and drop me off until my car is fixed.

653
00:50:45,920 --> 00:50:49,360
That won’t be a problem, will it… my dear counterparty?

654
00:50:50,120 --> 00:50:53,080
Fey texted to say she might not be coming anymore.

655
00:50:53,560 --> 00:50:55,880
If you're done eating, you can head back first, P'Flint

656
00:50:55,880 --> 00:50:58,880
So...would you mind if I stay at your place tonight?

657
00:50:59,720 --> 00:51:02,880
You actually remember that I like chamomile tea.

658
00:51:04,440 --> 00:51:06,080
Is that what you call a kiss?

659
00:51:07,080 --> 00:51:09,760
This is what you call a kiss.
